text:
I think the best thing we can do without placing any bets on the table is to simply just wait and see what happens with this now becoming knowledge.
Will Roblox find themselves being an easier target to sue?
Will there be privacy problems from this?
Will this help anyone?
(12/14)

But yeah, as to where I stand on this situation, I don't really know here.
Again, it's kinda like a double edged sword situation here I guess.
There's good to come out and bad to come out as well from this happening.
I don't really know what side to pick honestly.
(11/14)

So probably this was added just so Roblox can try to be safe from getting their 50th lawsuit since they seem to be getting sued left and right.
I don't really know what will happen with this in all honesty, since it's kinda difficult to tell what will happen with Roblox.
(9/14)

But I also seen some people speculate that Roblox isn't really gonna do much with this, or at all, since as already said this is VC recording documentation thing is a clause most companies with games or consoles with VC have to follow.
(8/14)

But I'm not gonna act like I know how ANY of this works, I'm just a random obscure nobody that plays Roblox talking about this situation on Twitter and giving my thoughts about it.
I'm probably the least experienced person to talk about this LMAO
(7/14)

(6/14)

Not to mention, some people CARE about their privacy online, and this being leaked could mean LESS privacy being given to the user. I mean you already give your ID to a random 3rd Party company in order to access VC in Roblox, already suspicious enough to some people.
(5/14)

And I feel like people who are innocent will probably get the boot.
Like, if you accidentally slip up and sware, which is most people would do when they are trying not to swear dispite it being normal in their vocabulary, you're probably gonna get in trouble for a mistake.
(4/14)

And this could PROBABLY weed out the Online Daters and other people trying to VERY ILLEGAL suspicious activities via Roblox VC on the platform.
(2/14)

I feel like this could be a double edged sword type of problem here.
On the one side: This probably isn't anything to worry about, most VC things like Xbox Live for example have this because it's a legal clause they NEED to follow.
